  <body>
      <section name="Download">
      <p>
        Jadabs is currently distributed in two versions. The minimal
        version includes the by default the service-manager configuration and
        can be used on small devices in a distributed 
        environment. In the full version we added the dAOP approach of PROSE
        and needs to be run more powerful linux machines.
      </p>
      
      <table>
          <tr><th>configuration</th><th>Description</th><th>AOP</th><th>download</th></tr>
          
          <tr>
          	<td>minimal</td>
          	<td>OSGi/Nanning, Service-Manager</td>
          	<td>AspectJ/Nanning</td>
          	<td><a href="https://developer.berlios.de/project/showfiles.php?group_id=2534">jadabs-x.x.x-minimal.tar.gz</a></td>
          </tr>
          
          <tr>
          	<td>prose</td>
          	<td>OSGi/Prose, JXME, Service-Manager</td>
          	<td>AspectJ/Nanning/Prose</td>
          	<td><a href="https://developer.berlios.de/project/showfiles.php?group_id=2534">jadabs-x.x.x-prose.tar.gz</a></td>
          </tr>
          
      </table>
      
    </section>
      
  	<section name="Start">
		<p>
			For a Quick-Start download one of the above releases.
		</p>
		
		<table><tr><th>Default Execution</th></tr></table>
<source><![CDATA[
linux> jadabs.sh
or
win32> jadabs.bat
or with the prose version
linux> jadabs.sh prose
]]>
</source>



  	</section>
  	
  	<subsection name="Configuration">
  	    <p>
  	        Configuration is performed in the jadabs.starter file by specifying
  	      the OPDs to be used. Check the <a href="model">Jadabs-model</a> for more information 
  	        about configuraiton and startup of your own plugins.
  	    </p>

  	</subsection>
  	
